        <p>
            The cogs in each mint range from level 10 to level 11, with the supervisor being level 12. The lowest cog
            type found in a cog mint is a Money Bags. The purpose of completing a cog mints is to collect cogbucks to 
            earn a promotion on a Cashbot suit. Coin Mints are typically used by lower level Cashbot suits, Dollar Mints are
            typically used by mid-level Cashbot suits such as the Bean Counter and Number Cruncher, and Bullion Mints are typically
            used by higher level Cashbot suits. Click <a href="#suit">here</a> to learn how to build a Cashbot suit.
        </p>
        <h4>Mint Floor Plans</h4>
        <p>
            Everytime a toon goes into a mint, most likely the floor plan will be different. It is not always the same
            layout like a Sellbot Factory is. There are 20 different types of floor plans per mint, each consisting of a different
            number of cogs and obstacles. In order to get to the next room, toons must overcome these obstacles or defeat the cogs 
            that are in the way.
        </p>
